text: Condé-en-Normandie is a commune. It is in the region Normandy in the Calvados department in the northwest of France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2016 and consists of the former communes of Condé-sur-Noireau (the seat), La Chapelle-Engerbold, Lénault, Proussy, Saint-Germain-du-Crioult and Saint-Pierre-la-Vieille.Arrêté préfectoral 1 December 2015 == References == Category:2016 establishments in France Category:Communes in Calvados
title: Condé-en-Normandie
